    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41467_023_39889_1__task_004/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The detected peaks are assessed by a set of quality metrics and retained only if the preset thresholds are met... SNR (signal-to-noise ratio) is often defined differently among tools. In asari, the noise for an elution peak is the average signal intensity of neighboring non-peak data points, 100 to each side; SNR is the ratio between peak height and noise... Together with peak shape, users can rely on them to routinely determine the peak quality.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms SNR and peak shape filtering exist and are used for quality control. However, the specific SNR threshold of >2 is not explicitly stated in passages. Peak shape threshold of >0.5 is mentioned ('by default, does not return peaks of bad shapes (under 0.5)' in passage 8). Prominence threshold of >20% is not mentioned; paper discusses 'prominence' as 'vertical distance of a peak top to its adjacent local minima' but no specific percentage threshold is given. Minimum peak height default of 1e5 is mentioned in passage 7 ('XCMS and asari used similar parameters (peak height > 1E5)') but as a comparison parameter, not asari's default.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_004",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does the peak quality filtering mechanism using SNR (>2), peak shape goodness-of-fit, and minimum peak height (default 1e5 with >20% prominence) thresholds reduce the number of detected features in the feature table?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:43:50.349643+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
