    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/composite-mass-track-construction/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The default peak detection algorithm in asari first estimates the baseline and noise level on a composite mass track (details in the Supplementary Information). The statistics drive the decisions on baseline subtraction, detrending or smoothing. Detrending is to regress out shifting chromatographic background, used sparingly in necessary tracks (e.g., Supplementary Fig. 8c). Noisy composite mass tracks are smoothed using simple moving average.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes the functionality (baseline/noise estimation, detrending, smoothing on composite mass tracks) but does not explicitly name the function 'asari peaks.audit_mass_track'. The function name is inferred by the extractor but not verbatim in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "composite-mass-track-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "asari peaks.audit_mass_track",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:48:09.947562+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/composite-mass-track-construction/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Retention time (RT) correction between samples, also called retention time alignment, is carried out by LOWESS regression, using a small subset of high-quality elution peaks.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms LOWESS regression is used for RT calibration in asari, but does not explicitly name the function 'asari chromatograms.rt_lowess_calibration'. The function name is inferred but not verbatim.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "composite-mass-track-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "asari chromatograms.rt_lowess_calibration",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:48:09.947562+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/composite-mass-track-construction/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Requires Python 3.8+.",
      "asbval:note": "Explicitly stated in passage 10.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "composite-mass-track-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Python 3.8+",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:48:09.947562+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/composite-mass-track-construction/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Aligned mass tracks across samples are corrected for RT, using LOWESS regression on a subset of high-quality elution peaks, then aggregated into composite mass tracks (b). All composite mass tracks are stored in the 'Composite Map'. Elution peak detection is performed on the composite mass tracks, and feature table is generated by looking up the corresponding peak areas in each individual sample.",
      "asbval:note": "Scope description aligns with the paper's workflow: RT calibration precedes composite mass track construction, which precedes peak detection.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "composite-mass-track-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When processing a multi-sample LC-MS metabolomics project after mass-track extraction and retention-time calibration have been applied to all individual samples, and you need to detect peaks across the entire cohort.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:48:09.947562+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/composite-mass-track-construction/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Because the composite mass track has higher signals than any individual sample, the quality of peak detection is often improved. In practical terms, detecting weak peaks will be enhanced by combining signals from multiple samples; irregularity such as chromatographic gap and bad peak shape will be ameliorated (example in Supplementary Fig. 2).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that composite mass track approach improves detection of weak peaks through signal pooling. Specific threshold of N > 10 is not stated in paper but is consistent with the principle.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "composite-mass-track-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This approach is especially valuable when N > 10 samples, as it avoids redundant peak-detection invocations and enables detection of low-abundance features visible only when signal is pooled across samples.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:48:09.947562+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/composite-mass-track-construction/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper does not discuss limitations related to ionization efficiency differences or sample load bias in composite mass track construction.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "composite-mass-track-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When input samples have drastically different ionization efficiency or sample loads (pooling may obscure sample-specific rare peaks or introduce bias toward dominant samples).",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:48:09.947562+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/composite-mass-track-construction/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "RT alignment has no impact on m/z alignment. In previous tools, if a feature is only present in one or few samples, correspondence becomes problematic. However, the presence of a single good elution peak is evidence that the analytical method is valid for that particular metabolite.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper acknowledges RT alignment importance and describes bidirectional RT remapping, implying that miscalibration would affect composite track quality. However, the paper does not explicitly state this as a limitation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "composite-mass-track-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When retention-time miscalibration across samples is severe (misaligned scans will blur the composite track and lower peak definition).",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:48:09.947562+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/computational-efficiency-single-pass-vs-repeated-detection/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "With this approach, elution peak detection is no longer required on individual samples. It can be done on the composite mass track, then the peak area is looked up in each individual sample and reported as feature intensity values (Fig. 2b). This greatly simplifies feature correspondence, and has a significant performance gain, by not repeating the computational cost of peak detection on all individual samples.",
      "asbval:note": "Core design principle of asari explicitly stated. Paper demonstrates computational improvement via composite mass track approach.",
