      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/computational-resource-profiling-and-benchmarking/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Computational efficiency is fundamentally important to\u2014omics data. For MZmine and MS-DIAL, processing 100 samples often becomes challenging on a desktop computer. XCMS is considered more performant and is the default choice of cloud computing. Here, the computational efficiency of asari is benchmarked against XCMS using multiple datasets of different sizes and platforms. Small studies can be processed by asari under a minute. Some studies of 100 ~ 200 samples take less than 10 min by asari using a single CPU core. Therefore, asari provides significant improvement of CPU time over XCMS by 1 ~ 2 orders of magnitude (Fig. 8a).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly benchmarks asari's computational performance across multiple datasets of different sizes and platforms, measuring CPU time and memory.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "computational-resource-profiling-and-benchmarking",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Systematically measure and characterize wall-clock runtime and peak memory consumption of a metabolomics processing tool across increasing sample cohort sizes to verify scalability claims and establish throughput benchmarks on target hardware.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:48:54.591067+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/computational-resource-profiling-and-benchmarking/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The CPU time and memory use was largely a linear function of sample numbers (Fig. 8b, c). The results indicate that the performance gap between XCMS and asari widens for larger studies. XCMS can also become more complicated if it goes beyond simple workflows or large studies are processed. The full SLAW dataset of >2000 samples was processed in the previous study by XCMS on a cluster node of 15 CPU cores in 7~12 h. This same dataset was processed in ~1 h on a regular laptop computer using asari.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper provides explicit scaling curves (Fig. 8b, c) showing linear scaling of CPU time and memory with sample count, and concrete throughput benchmarks (>2000 samples in ~1 h on laptop).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "computational-resource-profiling-and-benchmarking",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Throughput benchmarks (samples/hour or samples/minute) and memory scaling curves (MB or GB vs. sample count) demonstrating linear or sublinear growth",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:48:54.591067+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/computational-resource-profiling-and-benchmarking/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To test the scalability, we subset the SLAW data using varying sample numbers. The CPU time and memory use was largely a linear function of sample numbers (Fig. 8b, c).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly subsets the SLAW dataset with varying sample numbers to test scalability.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
