    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/feature-table-row-count-validation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Asari includes a set of metrics to fully describe data quality... SNR (signal-to-noise ratio)... peak shape... Together with peak shape, users can rely on them to routinely determine the peak quality... The detected peaks are assessed by a set of quality metrics and retained only if the preset thresholds are met.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes quality filtering using SNR, peak shape, and other metrics applied to detected peaks. The concept of comparing filtered vs. unfiltered results is implicit in the quality assessment workflow.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "feature-table-row-count-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Validate the effectiveness of peak quality filtering by comparing row counts between the full unfiltered feature table and the filtered feature table to confirm appropriate selectivity. This quantitative check ensures that filtering thresholds (SNR, peak shape, height, prominence",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:49:35.278157+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/feature-table-row-count-validation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The default peak detection algorithm in asari first estimates the baseline and noise level... peak height and prominence requirements dynamically determined on the segment statistics... The detected peaks are assessed by a set of quality metrics and retained only if the preset thresholds are met.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms SNR, peak shape (>0.5), and peak height thresholds are used. Prominence is mentioned as a concept ('vertical distance of a peak top to its adjacent local minima') but specific threshold values (SNR >2, prominence \u226520% of peak_height) are not explicitly stated in passages. Default peak height of 1e5 is mentioned in one benchmark context but not as a universal default.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "feature-table-row-count-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "parameters",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "SNR (>2), goodness-of-fit (peakshape > 0.5), minimum peak height (default 1e5), and prominence (\u226520% of peak_height) thresholds",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:49:35.278157+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/feature-table-row-count-validation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Asari is designed with a set of specific algorithmic framework and data structures, and all steps are explicitly trackable... These data structures are JSON compatible and exposed, so that advanced users and developers can reuse them easily.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms asari performs peak quality filtering and outputs feature tables. However, the specific file names 'full_Feature_table.tsv' and 'preferred_Feature_table.tsv' are not mentioned in the passages. The paper discusses feature table outputs but does not name these specific files.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
