    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-grid-construction-and-mapping/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Aligned mass tracks of all samples form a 'MassGrid', which provides a foundation for trackable and high-quality feature correspondence.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes MassGrid as the core data structure for mass track alignment. The conditional strategy selection (pairwise vs. clustering) is implied by the paper's discussion of scalability and the mention of nearest-neighbor clustering for larger studies, though not explicitly stated as a conditional threshold at \u226410 vs. >10 samples.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-grid-construction-and-mapping",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Construct a unified mass-to-sample alignment map (MassGrid) by conditionally selecting between pairwise or clustering-based alignment strategies based on study size, establishing consensus m/z values across samples while tracking sample membership and mass track identifiers.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:51:08.910183+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-grid-construction-and-mapping/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Mass tracks are aligned cross samples before elution peak detection in asari (Fig. 2a, right). This takes advantage of the superb mass resolution on today's instruments and avoids errors stemming from elution peak detection. Mass tracks lock in unique m/z values per sample, therefore greatly reducing the complexity of m/z alignment, compared to the alignment of individual elution peaks. The mass tracks that match 13 C/12 C and Na/H patterns are considered of high confidence and used as guides in the m/z alignment.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes mass track alignment and mentions that isotopic landmarks are used as guides, but does not explicitly specify the \u226410 vs. >10 sample threshold for switching between pairwise and clustering strategies. The scalability discussion (passage 10) shows linear scaling with sample numbers but does not name the specific threshold.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-grid-construction-and-mapping",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "After mass track extraction from individual LC-MS samples, when you need to align mass tracks across a cohort to produce a unified feature matrix. Specifically: when study size is \u226410 samples, use pairwise anchor-prioritized alignment; when >10 samples, switch to nearest-neighbor",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:51:08.910183+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-grid-construction-and-mapping/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "a nearest neighbor (NN) clustering is performed to establish the number of mass tracks.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper mentions nearest-neighbor clustering for mass track alignment but does not provide the exact function name 'nn_cluster_by_mz_seeds' or specify the >10 sample threshold. The function name and threshold appear to be inferred from code documentation not present in the paper passages.",
