      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Mass tracks are aligned cross samples before elution peak detection in asari (Fig. 2a, right). This takes advantage of the superb mass resolution on today's instruments and avoids errors stemming from elution peak detection. Mass tracks lock in unique m/z values per sample, therefore greatly reducing the complexity of m/z alignment, compared to the alignment of individual elution peaks.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes mass track alignment and MassGrid construction but does not explicitly detail the consensus m/z computation method as 'combining median and intensity-weighted estimates'. The paper states mass tracks are aligned and form a MassGrid, but the specific algorithmic approach to consensus m/z calculation (median vs. intensity-weighted) is not verbatim in the passages provided. The concept of consensus m/z values is implicit in mass track alignment but the specific methodology claimed is not explicitly stated.",
