    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/peak-evaluation-metrics-cselectivity-snr-gaussian-fit/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Together with peak shape, users can rely on them to routinely determine the peak quality... The mSelectivity metric (Fig. 1c) is integral to mass track construction and mass alignment in asari. Similar for chromatography, cSelectivity is defined as how distinct chromatograhic elution peaks are (Fig. 6b)... Signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) in asari is defined by peak height divided by noise level... An intuitive measure of peak quality is 'peak shape', here defined as the goodness of fitting to a Gaussian curve",
      "asbval:note": "All three quality metrics (cSelectivity, SNR, Gaussian fit/peak shape) are explicitly described in the paper as core quality assessment criteria for peak evaluation in asari.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "peak-evaluation-metrics-cselectivity-snr-gaussian-fit",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Evaluate detected peaks against three orthogonal quality criteria\u2014chromatographic selectivity (cSelectivity), signal-to-noise ratio (SNR > 2), and gaussian fit quality\u2014to retain only peaks meeting shape and signal thresholds.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:52:51.755904+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/peak-evaluation-metrics-cselectivity-snr-gaussian-fit/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "scipy.signal.find_peaks is not mentioned in the paper. The paper describes asari's own peak detection algorithm: 'The default peak detection algorithm in asari first estimates the baseline and noise level on a composite mass track... We use a local maximum search algorithm, with peak height and prominence requirements dynamically determined on the segment statistics.' No external scipy dependency is cited for peak detection.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "peak-evaluation-metrics-cselectivity-snr-gaussian-fit",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
