      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SNR (signal-to-noise ratio) is often defined differently among tools. In asari, the noise for an elution peak is the average signal intensity of neighboring non-peak data points, 100 to each side; SNR is the ratio between peak height and noise (Fig. 6a).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper defines SNR calculation method but does NOT specify SNR > 2 as a threshold. Paper discusses SNR as a quality metric and filtering criterion but does not name a specific SNR threshold value. The card claims a specific threshold (SNR > 2) that is not verbatim in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-023-39889-1",
